The skipper's body was found by police divers on Sunday after the vessel sank on Saturday. CAPE TOWN The body of a missing crew member from a boat that capsized has been found.The skipper's body was found by police divers on Sunday. The vessel sank in Table Bay while assisting a fishing boat to berth on Saturday.Two other crew members aboard the Troupant were saved and taken to hospital where one still remains.The National Sea Rescue Institute's (NSRI) s Craig Lambinon says: &quot;Police divers and fire rescue service divers continued with an ongoing search. During that operation, the body of a 60-year-old man who was missing was found inside the boat. He was declared deceased. Condolences have been conveyed to the family.&quot;(Edited by Tamsin Wort)